omic Bomb' \u2013 Tour Video by Giorgio Testi |website=Promonews |date=November 8, 2012 |accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"I Feel It in My Bones\"\n| Roboshobo<ref>{{cite web |last=Roffman |first=Michael |url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2012/12/video-the-killers-i-feel-it-in-my-bones/ |title=Video: The Killers \u2013 \"I Feel It In My Bones\" |website=[[Consequence of Sound]] |date=December 4, 2012 |accessdate=September 18, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Miss Atomic Bomb\"\n| Warren Fu<ref>{{cite web |last=Brown |first=Jimmy |url=https://www.promonews.tv/videos/2012/12/12/killers-miss-atomic-bomb-warren-fu/16078 |title=The Killers 'Miss Atomic Bomb' by Warren Fu |website=Promonews |date=December 12, 2012 |accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Here with Me\"\n| Tim Burton<ref>{{cite web |last=Knight |first=David |url=https://www.promonews.tv/videos/2012/12/20/killers-here-me-tim-burton/16205 |title=The Killers 'Here With Me' by Tim Burton |website=Promonews |date=December 20, 2012 |accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Shot at the Night\"\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2013\n| Roboshobo<ref>{{cite web |last=Cinquemani |first=Sal |url=https://www.slantmagazine.com/house/article/music-video-the-killers-shot-at-the-night |title=Music Video: The Killers, \"Shot at the Night\" |website=[[Slant Magazine]] |date=September 27, 2013 |accessdate=September 18, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Just Another Girl\"\n| Warren Fu<ref>{{cite web |last=Brown |first=Jimmy |url=https://www.promonews.tv/videos/2013/11/28/killers-just-another-girl-warren-fu/23064 |title=The Killers 'Just Another Girl' by Warren Fu |website=Promonews |date=November 28, 2013 |accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Christmas in L.A.\"<br>{{small|(featuring Dawes)}}\n| Kelly Loosli<ref>{{cite web |last=McGovern |first=Kyle |url=https://www.spin.com/2013/12/killers-christmas-in-la-owen-wilson-video/ |title=Watch Owen Wilson as a Holiday Sad Sack in the Killers' Somber 'Christmas in L.A.' Video |work=Spin |date=December 2, 2013 |accessdate=September 18, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Joel the Lump of Coal\"<br>{{small|(featuring Jimmy Kimmel)}}\n| 2014\n| [[Jonathan Kimmel]]<ref name=\"imvdb\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Dirt Sledding\"<br>{{small|(featuring Ryan Pardey and Richard Dreyfuss)}}\n| 2015\n| Matthew Gray Gubler<ref>{{cite web |last=Spanos |first=Brittany |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/watch-the-killers-santa-let-loose-in-dirt-sledding-christmas-video-20151201 |title=Watch the Killers, Santa Let Loose in 'Dirt Sledding' Christmas Video |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |date=December 1, 2015 |accessdate=September 18, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"The Man\" \n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2017\n| Tim Mattia<ref>{{cite web |last=Gottlieb |first=Steven |url=https://www.videostatic.com/watch-it/2017/06/28/killers-man-tim-mattia-dir |title=The Killers \"The Man\" (Tim Mattia, dir.) |website=VideoStatic |date=June 28, 2017 |accessdate=September 17, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Run for Cover\" \n| Tarik Mikou and Eric Morin<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.promonews.tv/videos/2017/08/29/killers-run-cover-tarik-mikou/49452 |title=The Killers 'Run For Cover' by Tarik Mikou |website=Promonews |date=August 29, 2017 |accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Rut\" \n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2018\n| Danny Drysdale<ref>{{cite web |last=Skinner |first=Tom |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/killers-unveil-emotional-video-rut-2217000 |title=The Killers unveil emotional video for 'Rut' |work=NME |date=January 10, 2018 |accessdate=April 25, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Wonderful Wonderful\" (lyric video)\n| Caitlyn Cutler<ref>{{cite web |url=https://caitlyncutler.com/music.html |title=Music |website=caitlyncutler.com |accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Land of the Free\" \n| 2019\n| [[Spike Lee]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Minsker |first1=Evan |last2=Strauss |first2=Matthew |url=https://pitchfork.com/news/the-killers-take-on-border-wall-mass-incarceration-on-new-song-land-of-the-free-listen/ |title=Spike Lee Directs the Killers' Video for New Song \"Land of the Free\": Watch |website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]] |date=January 14, 2019 |accessdate=January 15, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Caution\"\n| 2020\n| Sing Lee<ref>{{cite web |last=Bloom |first=Madison |url=https://pitchfork.com/news/watch-the-killers-new-caution-video/ |title=Watch the Killers' New \"Caution\" Video |website=Pitchfork |date=March 20, 2020 |accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{Notelist-ua}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.thekillersmusic.com/}}\n* {{AllMusic|id=the-killers-mn0000670226|label=The Killers}}\n* {{Discogs artist|The Killers|The Killers}}\n* {{MusicBrainz artist|id=95e1ead9-4d31-4808-a7ac-32c3614c116b|name=The Killers}}\n\n{{The Killers}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Killers Discography, The}}\n[[Category:Alternative rock discographies]]\n[[Category:Discographies of American artists]]\n[[Category:The Killers|Discography]]\n[[Category:Rock music group discographies|Killers, The]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox artist discography\n| Artist       = [[The Killers]]\n| Image        = KillersBrixton120917-47.jpg\n| Caption      = The Killers performing during the [[Wonderful Wonderful World Tour]] in September 2017\n| Studio       = 5\n| Live         = 1\n| Compilation  = 3\n| EP           = 1\n| Video        = 1\n| Singles      = 35\n| Music videos = 38\n| Option       = 4\n| Option name  = Promotional singles\n}}\n\nAmerican [[Rock music|rock]] band [[The Killers]] has released five [[studio album]]s, one [[live album]], three [[compilation album]]s, one [[extended play]], 35 [[Single (music)|singles]], four [[promotional single]]s, and 38 [[music video]]s. Part of the [[post-punk revival]] movement, The Killers are influenced by music styles of the 1980s and 1990s. The band has sold over 22 million records worldwide.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nme.com/photos/music-photos/40-things-you-never-knew-about-the-killers-1410300 |title=40 things you never knew about The Killers |work=[[NME]] |date=July 7, 2017 |accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref> The group's debut album, ''[[Hot Fuss]]'' (2004), brought the band mainstream success, spawning four UK top-20 singles, including \"[[Mr. Brightside]]\". The album has since been certified triple platinum by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA) and seven-times platinum by the [[British Phonographic Industry]] (BPI),<ref name=\"RIAA\"/><ref name=\"BPI\"/> selling seven million copies worldwide.<ref name=\"sfweekly\"/>\n\nThe Killers' second studio album, ''[[Sam's Town]]'', was released in October 2006, being met initially by mixed reviews but nonetheless proving a commercial success, debuting at number two on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] with opening sales of 315,000 units, and going on to be certified platinum by the RIAA.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1694785/the-killers-sams-town-album-anniversary.jhtml|title=The Killers' Sam's Town, Six Years Later: An American Masquerade|publisher=[[MTV News]]}}</ref> In the UK, the album debuted atop the chart and went on to be certified five-times platinum by the BPI.<ref name=\"BPI\"/> The compilation album ''[[Sawdust (album)|Sawdust]]'' was released in November 2007, containing [[B-side]]s, rarities, and new material.\n\nThe band's third album, ''[[Day & Age]]'', produced by [[Stuart Price]], was released in November 2008 and spawned the commercially successful single \"[[Human (The Killers song)|Human]]\", described by [[Brandon Flowers]] as \"our biggest song, pound for pound\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/entertainment/the-killers-are-dying-to-cut-loose/story-e6frewt9-1226396789096|title=Killers dying to cut loose|publisher=|accessdate=21 July 2017}}</ref> ''Day & Age'' proved a commercial success in Europe, was certified Gold by the RIAA.<ref name=\"RIAA\"/> Their fourth album, ''[[Battle Born (album)|Battle Born]]'', was released in September 2012, becoming the band's fourth consecutive album to reach number one in both the UK and Ireland.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a407706/the-killers-score-fourth-uk-no1-album-with-battle-born.html|title=The Killers score fourth UK No.1 album with 'Battle Born'|website=[[Digital Spy]]}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2013, in celebration of their first decade together, the band released their first [[greatest hits album]], titled ''[[Direct Hits (The Killers album)|Direct Hits]]'', a contractual requirement with their record label.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailystar.co.uk/showbiz/playlist/350479/The-Killers-are-red-faced-after-releasing-greatest-hits-album|title=The Killers are red-faced after releasing greatest hits album|work=[[Daily Star (United Kingdom)|Daily Star]]}}</ref> The compilation features two new tracks, including \"[[Shot at the Night]]\", produced by Anthony Gonzalez of [[M83 (band)|M83]]. In September 2017, The Killers released their fifth studio album, ''[[Wonderful Wonderful (The Killers album)|Wonderful Wonderful]]'', becoming the band's fifth consecutive album to top the UK Albums Chart,<ref>{{cite web|last=White|first=Jack|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/the-killers-set-new-official-chart-record-with-fifth-number-1-album-wonderful-wonderful__20603/|title=The Killers' Wonderful Wonderful becomes their fifth UK Number 1 album|publisher=Official Charts Company|date=September 29, 2017|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref> as well as their first number-one album on the US ''Billboard'' 200.<ref>{{cite web|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7981900/the-killers-first-no-1-album-billboard-200-chart-wonderful-wonderful|title=The Killers Earn First No. 1 Album on Billboard 200 Chart With 'Wonderful Wonderful'|work=Billboard|date=October 1, 2017|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Albums==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of studio albums, with selected chart positions, sales figures and certifications\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:8em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:18em;\"| Details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"10\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:11em;\"| Sales\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:13em;\"| [[List of music recording certifications|Certifications]]\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Billboard 200|US]]<br><ref name=\"US-albums\">{{cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/the-killers/chart-history/billboard-200 |title=The Killers Chart History: Billboard 200 |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=April 25, 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[ARIA Charts|AUS]]<br><ref name=\"AUS\">Peak chart positions in Australia:\n* All except noted: {{cite web |url=https://australian-charts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=The+Killers |title=Discography The Killers |website=australian-charts.com |accessdate=December 11, 2011}}\n* ''(Red) Christmas EP'': {{cite journal |url=https://webarchive.nla.gov.au/awa/20120116045620/http://pandora.nla.gov.au/pan/23790/20120116-1555/Issue1137.pdf |title=ARIA Top 100 Albums \u2013 Week Commencing 12th December 2011 |journal=[[The ARIA Report]] |issue=1137 |page=6 |date=December 12, 2011 |accessdate=March 28, 2020 |via=[[National Library of Australia]]}}\n* \"Tranquilize\": {{cite journal |url=https://webarchive.nla.gov.au/awa/20071119130000/http://pandora.nla.gov.au/pan/23790/20071120-0000/issue923.pdf |title=ARIA Top 100 Singles \u2013 Week Commencing 12th November 2007 |journal=The ARIA Report |issue=923 |page=4 |date=November 12, 2007 |accessdate=March 28, 2020 |vi