{"title_page": "List of FC Schalke 04 players", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n[[File:FC Schalke 04 Logo.svg|frameless|right|200px]]\n\n'''[[FC Schalke 04]]''' is a German football club based in [[Gelsenkirchen]]. The club was founded in 1904. They currently compete in the [[Bundesliga]].\n\nThe following are lists of Schalke 04 players since the formation of the Bundesliga in 1963 and notable club players of the pre-Bundesliga era.\n\n==Players==\n\n===Bundesliga era===\n{|class=wikitable\n!League!!Years\n|-\n|[[Bundesliga]]||1963\u20131981, 1982\u20131983, 1984\u20131988, 1991\u2013current\n|-\n|[[2. Bundesliga]]||1981\u20131982, 1983\u20131984, 1988\u20131991\n|}\n\nAll '''451''' players who made at least one appearance in a competitive match for Schalke 04 since August 1963 are listed below. 422 of them played in the Bundesliga. <br/>\n289 players scored at least one goal for the club. 260 of them found the net in the Bundesliga, which is a record for the league.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://10.en24.news/2019/fc-schalke-04-ozan-kabak-ensures-insanity-record-s04.html|title=FC Schalke 04: Ozan Kabak ensures insanity record|publisher=En24 News / Der Westen|date=5 November 2019}}</ref>\n\nCompetitive matches ''(2360 total)'' = [[Bundesliga]] ''(1755)'', [[2. Bundesliga]] ''(190)'', [[DFB-Pokal]] ''(195)'', [[DFL-Ligapokal|Ligapokal]] ''(22)'', [[DFL-Supercup|Supercup]] ''(2)'', [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] ''(70)'', [[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup/Europa League]] ''(100)'', [[UEFA Cup Winners' Cup|Cup Winners' Cup]] ''(14)'', [[UEFA Intertoto Cup|Intertoto Cup]] ''(12)''\n\n{{legend|#d3e7f8| Member of the Schalke 04 Hall of Fame (''\"Ehrenkabine\"'') \u2013 20 players (*)}}\n{{legend|#faecc8| Played for their senior national team in their Schalke 04 career \u2013 129 players, 36 for [[Germany national football team|Germany]] (# <nowiki>=</nowiki> international caps)}}\n{{legend|#d9d9d9| Still active for Schalke 04 \u2013 25 players (^)}}\n\n\u2022 Position (Pos): GK = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]], DF = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]], MF = [[Midfielder]], FW = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n\n''Statistics correct {{as of|2020|4|16|lc=y}}.''\n\n{|class=wikitable\n| [[#A|A]] \u2022 [[#B|B]] \u2022 [[#C|C]] \u2022 [[#D|D]] \u2022 [[#E|E]] \u2022 [[#F|F]] \u2022 [[#G|G]] \u2022 [[#H|H]] \u2022 [[#I|I]] \u2022 [[#J|J]] \u2022 [[#K|K]] \u2022 [[#L|L]] \u2022 [[#M|M]] \u2022 [[#N|N]] \u2022 [[#O|O]] \u2022 [[#P|P]] \u2022 [[#Q|Q]] \u2022 [[#R|R]] \u2022 [[#S|S]] \u2022 [[#T|T]] \u2022 [[#U|U]] \u2022 [[#V|V]] \u2022 [[#W|W]] \u2022 [[#Z|Z]]\n|}\n\n[[File:Klaus Fichtel.jpeg|thumb|200px|[[Klaus Fichtel]] made 556 appearances for Schalke between 1965 and 1988.]]\n[[File:Klaus Fischer 2013-06-29.jpg|thumb|200px|[[Klaus Fischer]] scored 226 goals in 349 appearances for Schalke between 1970 and 1981.]]\n[[File:Olaf Thon.jpeg|thumb|200px|[[Olaf Thon]] made 384 appearances for Schalke between 1983 and 2002.]]\n[[File:Gerald Asamoah \u2013 Tag der Legenden 2016 02.jpg|thumb|200px|[[Gerald Asamoah]] made 381 appearances for Schalke between 1999 and 2010.]]\n[[File:Ingo Anderbr\u00fcgge 2013.jpg|thumb|200px|[[Ingo Anderbr\u00fcgge]] made 355 appearances for Schalke between 1988 and 2000.]]\n[[File:Benedikt H\u00f6wedes 2011.jpg|thumb|200px|[[Benedikt H\u00f6wedes]] made 335 appearances for Schalke between 2007 and 2017.]]\n[[File:Jens Lehmann als Markenbotschafter Testimonial von SCHUNK cropped.jpg|thumb|200px|[[Jens Lehmann]] made 312 appearances for Schalke between 1988 and 1998.]]\n[[File:Mike B\u00fcskens 2012.jpg|thumb|200px|[[Mike B\u00fcskens]] made 302 appearances for Schalke between 1992 and 2002.]]\n[[File:Schalke Ebbe Sand 01.jpg|thumb|200px|[[Ebbe Sand]] scored 104 goals in 282 appearances for Schalke between 1999 and 2006.]]\n[[File:Klaas-Jan Huntelaar 2011.jpg|thumb|200px|[[Klaas-Jan Huntelaar]] scored 126 goals in 240 appearances for Schalke between 2010 and 2017.]]\n[[File:Marcelo Bordon.jpg|thumb|200px|[[Marcelo Bordon]] made 231 appearances for Schalke between 2004 and 2010.]]\n[[File:Raul Gonzalez Blanco Schalke.jpg|thumb|200px|[[Ra\u00fal (footballer)|Ra\u00fal]] scored 40 goals in 98 appearances for Schalke between 2010 and 2012.]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!colspan=2|Player!!colspan=2|Nationality!!rowspan=2|Pos!!colspan=2|Years!!colspan=2|Bundesliga /<br/>2. Bundesliga!!colspan=2|Competitive<br/>total\n|-\n!Name!!!!Nation!!data-sort-type=\"number\"|#!!Schalke 04 career!!!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|align=left colspan=2|{{Anchor|A}}{{sortname|Hans-Joachim|Abel}}||align=left colspan=2|{{flagicon|GER}}||{{sort|D|FW}}||colspan=2|1982\u20131984||63||23||73||29\n|-\n|align=left colspan=2|{{sortname|Mathias|Abel}}||align=left colspan=2|{{flagicon|GER}}||{{sort|B|DF}}||colspan=2|2006||1||0||4||0\n|-\n|align=left bgcolor=d3e7f8|{{sortname|R\u00fcdiger|Abramczik}}||bgcolor=d3e7f8|*||align=left bgcolor=faecc8|{{fbicon|GER}}||bgcolor=faecc8|<small>19</small>||{{sort|D|FW}}||colspan=2|1973\u20131980, 1987\u20131988||202||44||235||58\n|-\n|align=left colspan=2|{{sortname|Volker|Abramczik}}||align=left colspan=2|{{flagicon|GER}}||{{sort|D|FW}}||colspan=2|1981\u20131984||55||13||61||13\n|-\n|align=left colspan=2|{{sortname|Ibrahim|Afellay}}||align=left bgcolor=faecc8|{{fbicon|NED}}||bgcolor=faecc8|<small>3</small>||{{sort|C|MF}}||colspan=2|2012\u20132013||10||2||15||4\n|-\n|align=left colspan=2|{{sortname|Victor|Agali}}||align=left bgcolor=faecc8|{{fbicon|NGR}}||bgcolor=faecc8|<small>7</small>||{{sort|D|FW}}||colspan=2|2001\u20132004||54||14||74||20\n|-\n|align=left colspan=2|{{sortname||A\u00edlton|A\u00edlton (footballer, born 1973)}}||align=left colspan=2|{{flagicon|BRA}}||{{sort|D|FW}}||colspan=2|2004\u20132005||29||14||44||20\n|-\n|align=left colspan=2|{{sortname|J\u00f6rg|Albracht}}||align=left colspan=2|{{flagicon|GER}}||{{sort|A|GK}}||colspan=2|1994\u20131996||2||0|